.H 2 "relative_dirname"
This function requires one or more arguments,
the names of files which will have their directory parts extracted.
.H 3 "Example"
.TS
center;
l l.
Expression      Result
_
[relative_dirname a]    .
[relative_dirname a/b]  a
[relative_dirname a/b/c]        a/b
.TE
See \fIdirname\fP if you want to climb the directory tree with repeated
applications, \fIrelative_dirname\fP will continue to return ``.'' once
the current directory is reached.
.H 3 "See Also"
